Comment.Text: The matrices can then be converted in feature vectors.
The signal is then splitted in blocks of 1 second every 16th second and the logarithmic band power is computed thanks to the two Simple DSP and the Signal Average boxes.
Then the Stimulation Based Epoching box is used to select four seconds of signal half a second after the instruction was shown to the user (OVTK_GDF_Left and OVTK_GDF_Right).
The EEG signal is filtered in a large frequency band [8-30 Hz]
When finished player controller closes the scenario

This scenario should be used to train the LDA Classifier used to detect left / right hand movements. Load the Acquistion.xml data previously used and the CSP Spatial Filter. At the end of the training, an estimation of the classifier performance printed in the console. If this performance is lower than 65%, just run a new Acquisition.xml session to have better results.
The Classifier Trainer box produces a configuration file at the end of the experiment which will be used during online sessions.
The CSP Spatial Filter produced in the previous scenario is used prior to the feature extraction.
